They were once happily married. They even went as far as flaunting their marital bliss on social media. Then everything changed. Here are five celebrities whose marriages crashed after massive flaunt on social media: In July 2013, Toyin Abraham got married to Adeniyi Johnson. The party attracted Nollywood actors. The couple did not only flaunt themselves on social media but also went as far as playing couple’s roles in several movies after then. However, the actress filed for divorce on the grounds of infidelity in August 2015.    Seven famous Nigerian artistes off the radar     I’m satisfied with growth of comedy industry – Yaw     Femi Otedola reacts to daughter’s engagement to Mr…   On June 10, 2021, Nkechi Blessing posted their supposed wedding pictures on Opeyemi Falegan’s birthday following speculations she was married to him. Prior to that time, the 33-year-old actress has been constantly posting pictures and videos flaunting her new man on Instagram with captions portraying them as engaged. However, the actress and the estranged husband recently caused brouhaha on social media by announcing they have gone separate ways.         The multi-talented dancer got married to Dr. Justin Dean, an American sports therapist and a chiropractor. Kora used her Instagram account to promote her craft and how her husband constantly supports her. Justin Dean recently filed for divorce stating: “This is honestly the hardest decision of my life, but necessary. I’m walking away from this marriage for my mental health and to be the best version of myself.”       The actress got married to Lanre Gentry and often flaunted Gentry online till they divorced in September 2017.       The popular pop star was married to Tunji “Tee Billz” Balogun on November 23, 2013. On 28 April 2016, Balogun accused his wife of infidelity and his mother-in-law of witchcraft on 28 April. The couple divorced in 2018.